Preparations are in top gear for the swearing-in ceremony of Wajir Deputy Governor Ahmed Ali Muktar (pictured) any time now, as the Governor of Wajir County.  The ceremony will take place at the Wajir County Headquarters.  Muktar will replace Mohamed Abdi Mohamud who was impeached by Members of the Wajir County Assembly on April 27.  In a gazette notice, Senate Speaker Kenneth Lusaka notified the public of Mohamud’s removal from office on grounds of gross violation of the Constitution.  Senate to decide Wajir Governor Mohamud Abdi’s fate Monday  Fake News: No committee formed to deliberate on Governor Waiguru's impeachment  Sharp focus on Speaker Lusaka after the ouster of Murkomen and Kihika  Counties told to pay out billions in pending bills The Governor’s impeachment trial was held by an 11-member Committee chaired by Nyamira Senator Okong’o Omogeni.  Mohamud was found guilty of contravening the County Government Act 2012, the Public Procurement and Disposal Act 2015 and the Public Finance Management Act 2012.  The committee, however, absolved the governor from abuse of office and Gross Misconduct charges, saying MCAs did not provide sufficient evidence.  Take a quick survey and help us improve our website! They dropped 16 of the 17 allegations that he was facing and in its final report recommended his removal.  During the vote in a special sitting on May 17, 25 Senators supported the motion, two were against it while four abstained.  Mohamud was impeached on Tuesday, April 27, after 37 MCAs voted in favour of his ouster, while 10 opposed.   Homa Bay Senator Moses to record statement over corruption allegations   Senate Speaker Kenneth Lusaka:We have put in place systems to ensure voters aren't disturbed  Senate Speaker Kenneth Lusaka receives warm reception in Bungoma By Fred Kagonye | 1 hour ago By Mate Tongola | 1 day ago By Patrick Vidija | 11 days ago By Michael Saitoti | 15 days ago Ruto, Raila and Matiang’i lock horns in Bonchari by-election